-- Bank of Nova Scotia Executive Minicucci Resigns, to Be Replaced by Norfolk
-- Sean B. Pasternak
-- 2010-07-30T19:26:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/bank-of-nova-scotia-executive-minicucci-resigns-to-be-replaced-by-norfolk.html

          
          
             Pasquale Minicucci , a senior-vice
president of international banking for  Bank of Nova Scotia ’s
Caribbean business, resigned from Canada’s third-largest bank
last week.  
 Minicucci’s responsibilities will be handled by  Claude Norfolk , a senior vice-president at the Toronto-based bank,
Scotiabank spokeswoman  Ann DeRabbie  said.  
 Scotiabank has more than 200 branches in the Caribbean,
including operations in Aruba, Puerto Rico and Trinidad &
Tobago, according to its  website .  
